The paper discusses the development of analog-digital neuromorphic circuits, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The circuits are optimized for a specific technology, which suggests the category of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). The paper also mentions the implementation of different types of spiking neural network architectures, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and robotics (cs.AR). The techniques used for maximizing density and minimizing leakage current suggest the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses circuit simulation results, which suggests the category of electromagnetics (cs.EM).
